    <section id="sect-00003">
    <title>Type conversion with bool()</title>
    <para id="para-00010">Deciding whether a value is True or False is helpful when writing programs/statements based on decisions. Converting data types to booleans can seem unintuitive at first. Ex: Is "ice cream" True? But the conversion is actually simple.</para>
    <para id="para-00011"><term id="term-00002">bool()</term> converts a value to a boolean value, True or False.
    <list id="list-00002">
    <item><code class="python inline-code">True</code>: any non-zero number, any non-empty string</item>
    <item><code class="python inline-code">False</code>: 0, empty string</item>
    </list></para>
