    <note id="note-00008">
    <title>= vs ==</title>
    <para id="para-00030">A common mistake is using '=' for comparison instead of '=='. Ex: <code class="python inline-code">is_zero = num=0</code> will always assign is_zero and num with 0, regardless of num's original value. '=' performs assignment and will modify the variable. '==' performs comparison, does not modify the variable, and produces True or False.</para>
    </note>
